Dayo, the kidnapped son of immediate past Minister of Health, Prof. Isaac Adewole, has regained freedom from his abductors on Tuesday evening. He was kidnapped around 6pm on Monday in his farmland in Oyo State. Adewole, in a statement he personally signed, expressed his appreciation to President and Commander in Chief of the Armed Forces Muhammadu Buhari; Vice President Yemi Osinbajo; the Chief of Army Staff Lt. General Tukur Buratai; the acting IGP Mohammed Adamu; the DG of SSS Yusuf Magaji Bichi; all other security agencies & Vigilantes as well as all serving and former governors. “I must equally thank the AIG of Zone 11 Leye Oyeboade, the Oyo State Commissioner of Police Shina Olukolu, Garrison Commander of 2nd Division of the Nigerian Army, Director of SSS & Operation Burst in Oyo State, Head of IGP Anti – Kidnapping Squad, Traditional and religious leaders, members and staff of the federal ministry of health and other parastatal under the health ministry, journalists across the country,” he stated. The abductee, Dayo Adewole, a UK- trained Biochemist- turned farmer was kidnapped on his farm on Monday.